50	/**
51	 * Builds an RFC 6266 / RFC 5987 compliant `Content-Disposition` value.
52	 *
53	 * Always emits the ASCII `filename="..."` fallback for legacy clients. When
54	 * the original name contains non-ASCII or other characters that would be
55	 * stripped by sanitisation, also emits `filename*=UTF-8''<percent-encoded>`
56	 * so modern browsers (RFC 5987-aware) preserve the original name.
